{"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSToolBarTop","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The top toolbar (aka "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"navigation bar","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" on iOS and iPadOS 18 and lower) sits at the top of the screen and provides contextual information","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and controls related to the current view.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It typically displays the page title, and may include navigation actions such as “Back” or “Close” as well as supplementary actions.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It can contains leading and trailing actions.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSToolBarTop\/init(title:hasLargeTitle:subtitle:leadingItems:trailingItems:)"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSToolBarTop\/body(content:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods"},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSToolBarTop\/ViewModifier-Implementations"]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI12ViewModifierP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"OUDSToolBarTop","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"toolBarTop(_:hasLargeTitle:subtitle:leadingItems:trailingItems:)"},{"type":"text","text":"  View helper applies a SwiftUI toolbar configuration."}]},{"anchor":"Appearances","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Appearances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With Liquid Glass \/ iOS 26+ the OS will change the rendering of the toolbar items depending to the context:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The OS can group the items of same types in one group with kind of rectangle (e.g. views with menus)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"But for buttons items they will remain isolated"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The placement of the title can be leading or centered depending to the length of the text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The text can be truncated if there is not enough remaining space"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The OS can apply another style for the back button"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Without Liquid Glass \/ iOS 18 and lower, the OS won’t change that much the style of the toolbar items, Items won’t be visually grouped."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Globaly the appearence of the * navigation bar* elements is changed by the "},{"code":"oudsNavigationBarAppearance","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"helper of "},{"code":"View","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that must be applyed on the root view of the "},{"code":"NavigationStack","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for example."}]},{"anchor":"Technical-constraints","text":"Technical constraints","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To be sure for iOS 18 and lower the back buttton and text have the good color, in your main view apply the following accent color:"}]},{"code":["    struct AppMainView: View {","        var body: some View {","            ContentView()","                .accentColor(theme.colors.contentDefault)","        }","    }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Platform-considerations","text":"Platform considerations","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component is available on iOS, iPadOS, and visionOS"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component is not available for watchOS, tvOS and macOS"}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Badges-uses","text":"Badges uses","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For iOS 26 with Liquid Glass, the system badge is used because the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBadge","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" does not provide a suitable rendering with the glassified effect applied on the top toolbar."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For iOS until 18 and without Liquid Glass "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBadge","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is always used."}]},{"anchor":"Code-sample","text":"Code sample","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"code":["    ContentView()","        .toolBarTop(\"Title\",","            leadingItems: {","                OUDSToolBarItem(navigation: .back())","            },","            trailing